==============================================================
  EXAMPLE — Nexus Mods Provider
  THIS FILE IS AN EXAMPLE ONLY. It will do nothing here in
  the repo root. To use it:
  1. Copy this file into the mod folder you want to auto-update.
  2. Rename it to exactly  update.json  (remove "NexusModsExample-").
  3. Edit the values below ==== to match the mod's Nexus Mods page.
  4. Make sure your Nexus API key is set in the Auto Mod Updater's
     in-game settings (only needs to be done once).
     To get your API key, go to https://www.nexusmods.com/users/myaccount?tab=api+keys
     and copy your Personal API Key.

  NOTE: update.json is automatically preserved across updates —
  the updater backs it up and restores it, so you will not lose
  your config when the mod itself gets updated.

  FIELD REFERENCE:
  - "provider"               Must be "nexus". (Required)
  - "mod_id"                 The numeric mod ID from the Nexus URL.
                             e.g. nexusmods.com/balatro/mods/12345 → 12345. (Required)
  - "game_domain"            The Nexus game domain string.
                             Defaults to "balatro" if omitted. (Optional)
  - "strip_single_top_folder" If true (default), and the zip contains exactly one
                             top-level folder, its contents are extracted directly into
                             the mod folder instead of creating a nested sub-folder.
                             Set to false to disable this behaviour. (Optional)
==============================================================

{
    "provider":                 "nexus",
    "mod_id":                   12345,
    "game_domain":              "balatro",
    "strip_single_top_folder":  true
}
